children.name: MPPT
children.label: MPPT
children.description: Device is auto tracking maximum power point

children.name: THROTTLED
children.label: Throttled
children.description: Device is operating at reduced power output

children.name: FOLLOWING
children.label: Following
children.description: Device is running in grid following mode

children.name: FORMING
children.label: Forming
children.description: Device is running in grid forming mode

children.name: RECONNECT_DELAY
children.label: Reconnect Delay
children.description: Grid available, but Device is waiting for reconnect delay to expire

children.name: AREA_EPS_LOST
children.label: Area EPS Loss
children.description: Disconnected from grid due to abnormal grid condition(s)

children.name: CHARGE
children.label: Charging DC
children.description: Charging DC link.  AC side operating as a passive rectifier

children.name: RIDETHRU
children.label: Ride Through
children.description: High/Low Voltage or Frequency ride-through condition active

children.name: CESSATION
children.label: Momentary Cessation
children.description: Momentary power cessation active due to high/low grid frequency or voltage

children.name: AC_PWR_AVAIL
children.label: AC Power Available
children.description: Indicates that AC power is connected and that voltage and frequency are within nominal ranges.

children.name: DC_PWR_AVAIL
children.label: DC Power Available
children.description: Indicates that DC bus voltage is within operating range.

children.name: PWR_CRCT_EN
children.label: Power Circuit Enabled
children.description: Indicates whether the switching devices are active.

children.name: CTL_MSG_VALID
children.label: Control commands valid
children.description: Indicates the validity of the control bits. Message must be received within the serial timeout and parameter data within range to be considered valid.

children.name: PWR_CMD_VALID
children.label: Power command Valid
children.description: Indicates the validity of the real and reactive power commands.

children.name: CUR_CMD_VALID
children.label: Current command Valid
children.description: Indicates the validity of the real and reactive current commands

children.name: PH_ROTAT_STAT
children.label: Phase rotation status
children.description: Phase rotation order.  When L1 phase angle leads L2 phase angle, rotation is considered positive.

children.name: LV_DETECTED
children.label: Line voltage detected
children.description: Flag indicating if voltage is detected on L1, L2 or L3.

children.name: REM_AC_AVAIL
children.label: Remote AC Power Available
children.description: Indicates that remote AC power is connected and that voltage and frequency are within nominal ranges.

children.name: REM_PH_ROTAT_STAT
children.label: Remote phase rotation status
children.description: Remote phase rotation order.  When L1 phase angle leads L2 phase angle, rotation is considered positive.

children.name: REM_LV_DETECTED
children.label: Remote Line Voltage Detected
children.description: Flag indicating if voltage is detected on remote L1, L2 or L3.

children.name: DC_CMD_VALID
children.label: DC link reference commands Valid
children.description: Indicates the validity of the DC Bus reference commands.

children.name: En
children.label: Enable
children.description: Run command.  When set to a value of 'Enable', causes transition to grid forming or grid following mode depending on whether AC power is detected.  Must be set to 'Disable' to leave POR or FAULTED state.

children.name: VsenseRem
children.label: Use Voltage Sense as Remote
children.description: Use voltage sense input as either local or remote reference.

children.name: RemoteSync
children.label: Sync to Remote Source
children.description: Sync and connect to remote source.

children.name: ForceMX1
children.label: Close MX1
children.description: If set to 'Force On,' will force the relay closed, overriding firmware state machine commands.  Meant for diagnostic purposes only.

children.name: ForceMX2
children.label: Close MX2
children.description: If set to 'Force On,' will force the relay closed, overriding firmware state machine commands.  Meant for diagnostic purposes only.

children.name: ForceK1
children.label: Close K1
children.description: If set to 'Force On,' will force the relay closed, overriding firmware state machine commands.  Meant for diagnostic purposes only.

children.name: ForceK2
children.label: Close K2
children.description: If set to 'Force On,' will force the relay closed, overriding firmware state machine commands.  Meant for diagnostic purposes only.

children.name: ForceFan
children.label: Force Fan On
children.description: Forces cooling fan on (air cooled units only)

children.name: InvertHwEnable
children.label: Invert Hardware Enable
children.description: Inverts the logic of the Hardware Enable input.

children.name: EnableUps
children.label: Enable UPS Mode
children.description: Enables uninterruptible operation when transitioning from GRID FOLLOWING to GRID FORMING operation.  If operating in GRID FOLLOWING mode, and AC grid voltage is interrupted, the module will transition to GRID FORMING mode, with no interruption in power.

children.name: EnableSplitPhase
children.label: Enable Split Phase Mode
children.description: Dictates to the module whether it is connected to a three-phase (four wire) or split phase (L1, L2 and N) electrical system.

children.name: PhaseRotation
children.label: Phase Rotation Direction
children.description: Specifies phase rotation direction.  Only active while transitioning from READY to GRID_FORMING.

children.name: CAN
children.label: CAN control
children.description: CAN is the primary control source, though Modbus monitoring is still active

children.name: Modbus
children.label: Modbus control
children.description: Modbus is the primary control source, though CAN communication is still active.

children.name: Save
children.label: Save NV
children.description: Store non-volatile parameters to memory (present settings will persist power cycle.

children.name: Trans
children.label: Illegal transition
children.description: Illegal state transition requested by master
